A researcher wants to analyze the heights of a group of students in their class. However, the data contains some outliers due to errors in measurement. The researcher decides to use the median as a measure of central tendency since it is more robust than the mean. The heights of the 12 students in the class (in inches) are:

{63, 65, 61, 59, 73, 71, 68, 55, 69, 66, 62, 81}

Find the median height of the class, and compare it to the mean height (to illustrate the effect of outliers on measures of central tendency).
